root.data: The indicator “birth rate between 10-19 years old” is compiled from data sources of the Population and Housing Census (10-year cycle), the mid-term population and housing census (period of 10-19 years). 5-year period) and extrapolated from the results of the annual population change - family planning sample survey. These Census and Census are all part of the National Statistical Census Program
